		\itemch $\displaystyle\int\limits (x^3+x) \mathrm{d} x=\dfrac{x^4}{4}+\dfrac{x^2}{2}+C$.\\
		Theo đề bài ta có $F(0)=2 \Leftrightarrow \dfrac{0^4}{4}+\dfrac{0^2}{2}+C=2 \Leftrightarrow C=2$.\\
		Vậy $F(x)=\dfrac{x^4}{4}+\dfrac{x^2}{2}+2$.
